<% content_for :pagetitle do %>Privacy<% end %>
<% content_for :pagehead do %>

<section class="content featured-content-grad no-pad">
  	<div class="container colgroup">
	  	<div class="col6 bump-left under-right hide-on-mobile"><%= image_tag 'privacy_privacy.jpg', :height=>'350' %></div>
	  	<div class="col6  featured-content-textarea light-text pull-right">
	  		<div class="featured-content-textarea-inner">
	  			<h1>Foot-traffic analysis and customer privacy</h1>
	  			<p>Euclid measures foot-traffic anonymously by sensing the presence of smartphones without identifying individuals. We have no intention of capturing personal information.</p>
	  			<p><a href="http://blog.euclidelements.com/2013/07/why-i-built-euclid.html">Thoughts on privacy from our CEO</a></p>
	  			<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KZRMA3kDsVk" title="Euclid Privacy" data-height="500" class="btn no-top-marg arrow-btn dark-btn lightbox">Watch Video</a></p>
	  		</div>
	  	</div>
	</div>
</section>

<% end %>
<section class="content">
  <div class="container">
  	<div class="subcontainer9 pull-center">
	  	
	  	<ul class="content-list">
	  		<li class="content-list-item">
	  			<div class="col9">
	  				<div class="content-list-item-title sectionlabel">Mobile Location Analytics Code of Conduct</div>
	  				<p>In an effort to protect consumer privacy, New York Senator Charles Schumer and the Future of Privacy Forum, along with the help of Euclid Analytics CEO Will Smith and other leading technology leaders, recently developed the Mobile Location Analytics <a href="http://blog.euclidelements.com/2013/10/senator-schumer-and-tech-companies.html">Code of Conduct</a>. This code has established an industry-wide standard for protecting the privacy of consumers when dealing with their mobile device data. It also defines rules of engagement for retailers and technology companies to inform consumers about foot-traffic analysis and provide an easy way to opt out. </p>
	  			</div>
	  		</li>
	  		<li class="content-list-item">
	  			<%= image_tag 'privacy/privacy02.png', :class=> 'col3' %>
	  			<div class="col6">
	  				<div class="content-list-item-title sectionlabel">NO PERSONAL INFORMATION, NO IDENTIFYING DATA </div>
	  				<p>The reports we provide to retailers do not include any personal information. We make no attempts to link any data, behavioral or otherwise, to individual people.</p>
	  				<p><a href="../../img/privacy/report.png" title="Example Report" class="lightbox no-hover">View an example report</a></p>
	  			</div>
	  		</li>
	  		<li class="content-list-item">
	  			<%= image_tag 'privacy/privacy01.png', :class=> 'col3' %>
	  			<div class="col6">
	  				<div class="content-list-item-title sectionlabel">Limited data collection</div>
	  				<p>Our sensors collect only basic device information that is broadcast by Wi-Fi enabled phones. This does not include any sensitive data such as who you are, whom you call, or the websites you visit. </p>
	  			</div>
	  		</li>
	  		<li class="content-list-item">
	  			<%= image_tag 'privacy/privacy03.png', :class=> 'col3' %>
	  			<div class="col6">
	  				<div class="content-list-item-title sectionlabel">Easy opt-out and DELETION</div>
	  				<p>Shoppers with any concerns can easily opt out of participation and delete all of their existing data from our servers by clicking the button below. We also provide opt-out instructions at every store that uses our service.</p>
	  				<%= link_to_signupsite('optout', 'Opt-out', 'btn dark-btn') %>
	  			</div>
	  		</li>

	  		<li class="content-list-item">
	  			<%= image_tag 'privacy/privacy04.jpg', :class=> 'col3' %>
	  			<div class="col6">
	  				<div class="content-list-item-title sectionlabel">IN-STORE NOTICES</div>
	  				<p>To fully inform shoppers about foot-traffic analysis, we provide guidelines for retailers who use our service to post notices clearly in their stores.</p>
	  				<p><a href="../../resources/notice_guide.pdf" title="Notice Guidelines">View an example notice</a></p>
	  			</div>
	  		</li>
	  	</ul>
	  </div>
	</div>
</section>

